<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11469] Camel-Hipchat - Configure via xml is broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11469</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Declaring a hipchat endpoint in XML misconfigures the same component in the DSL. This seems to be because at some point via XML the component URI get&apos;s normalized and &apos;//&apos; is introduced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means a component of &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;to uri=&quot;hipchat:https:myhipchatserver.com:443?authToken?=abc&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is actually configured to the default api.hipchat.com.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
